Package: chiPlusZ
Title: Chi-Square Tests with SPSS-Style Column Proportion Z-Tests
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Gabija", "Vaitkevičiūtė", email = "info@biomatika.lt", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides an R implementation of SPSS's "Compare Column 
    Proportions" procedure for two-way contingency tables. Given a 
    long-format data frame, the package builds a contingency table, 
    performs a Chi-squared test of independence, computes Cramér's V 
    as an effect size measure, and runs pairwise column-proportion 
    Z-tests with Bonferroni correction. Results are summarised using 
    compact letter displays (CLD), where columns sharing a letter do 
    not differ significantly in their proportions. An optional export 
    to a formatted Excel workbook is provided, containing the 
    Chi-squared statistics, Cramér's V, observed and expected counts, 
    row percentages, CLD letters, and a pairwise comparison table with 
    significant comparisons highlighted.
